/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Flagship solutions preview — illustrated portrait tiles.

   Anatomy per tile:
   1. Title row   — family name + corner arrow
   2. Descriptor  — one editorial line about the family's character
   3. Icon        — a line-art emblem floating on the continuous
                    atmospheric wave flow, tinted by the family accent
                    through `currentColor`.

   The four tiles share one wave composition (the waves run
   edge-to-edge across the row as if cut from a single ribbon) — the
   visual analogue of "one operation, four families."

   The Solutions Hub is where the full list of modes lives. The
   homepage preview's job is to identify each family and invite the
   click — not to reprint the hub.
   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

const SECTION_EYEBROW = "What we move";
const SECTION_TITLE = "Four ways we move freight.";
const SECTION_SUPPORT =
  "Four operating families, each built around the lane, equipment, timing, and compliance demands of the freight.";

const FOCUS_RING =
  "focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[color:var(--color-menu-accent)] focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-[color:var(--color-surface-1)]";

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Continuous atmospheric flow — one shared wave composition that
   runs across all four tiles as a single editorial piece, tinted by
   each tile's own accent.

   How the continuity works:
   • Each tile renders the SAME svg, sized to `totalCards * 100%` of
     the tile width — so the svg is four tile-widths wide.
   • Each tile shifts it left by `(cardIndex / totalCards) × 100%` of
     the svg's OWN width, which equals exactly one tile-width per
     step. The wave curve that exits tile A's right edge re-enters
     tile B's left edge, seamless.

   How the color carries:
   • Both wave layers paint in `var(--card-accent)` (the tile-scoped
     accent). The shape flows unbroken across the ensemble; the hue
     shifts as the ribbon crosses each family boundary, so every
     card's waves, wash, and illustration share one chromatic family
     — cyan for Core Freight & Cross-Border, brand-red for
     Specialized, teal for Managed Logistics.
   • Kept to low fill-opacity (band 0.09, accent 0.22) so the waves
     read as tinted air and light, never as paint.
   • The original svg's opaque white "gutter" path is intentionally
     removed — we want the family wash underneath to glow through
     the negative space between wave bands.
   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

